## Future Improvements
### Breadcrumb Schema
Structured data (JSON-LD) telling Google how pages are hierarchically organized. Can show breadcrumb trail in search results (e.g., "Home > Pages > Developer"). Most useful for sites with deep navigation hierarchies. For a flat site with 4-5 pages, the SEO benefit is minimal.

### E2E Tests (Playwright/Cypress)
Automated browser tests that click through your site, catching visual regressions and broken interactions before deploy. Most useful for sites with complex interactions or frequent changes. For a mostly static HTML site with minimal JS interactivity, the current HTML validation and link checking tests are likely sufficient.
